<TITLE> Five die in Savar road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)Five people died and 50 were injured Wednesday in a road accident on Dhaka-Aricha highway in Savar, police said. The injured have been taken to different hospitals in Dhaka and Savar. Twenty of them are living in critical condition, doctors said. The police expected the death toll to rise. Police and witnesses said a Dhaka-bound Zaker Paribahan bus careened out of control into a roadside ditch after it hit a tree while giving the right of way to another bus. The bus was crumpled badly leaving the driver and two passengers dead on the spot. Two others died right in front of a local hospital. Senior police and army officers and Savar upazila executive officer Pranab Kumar Ghosh visited the injured in hospital and the accident site. The dead are yet to be identified, said Savar police chief Abul Khair Fakir. bdnews24
